  "footnotes": [
    "Pacta Conventa (1102): Agreement between Hungarian King Coloman and Croatian nobles by which Croatia entered personal union with Hungary while retaining its own laws and institutions.",
    "Republic of Ragusa (Dubrovnik, 1358–1808): A maritime republic that maintained independence from Venice by paying tribute to Ottoman Empire; a major Adriatic trading power.",
    "Military Frontier (Vojna Krajina, 1593–1881): A Habsburg-administered military zone along the Ottoman border, staffed by Serb, Croatian, and Vlach settlers in exchange for military service.",
    "Istrian Zone B: After WWII Istria was divided into Italian Zone A (Trieste) and Yugoslav Zone B; Zone B transferred to Yugoslavia in 1954, confirmed by Treaty of Osimo (1975).",
    "Republic of Serbian Krajina (RSK, 1991–95): Serb-held enclave in Croatia's Krajina and eastern Slavonia; collapsed after Croatian Operation Storm (1995); eastern Slavonia reunified via UNTAES (1998).",
    "S = eastern Slavonian plain · P = Pula/Istria peninsula · D = Dalmatian coast (source footnote)"
  ]
